OVERVIEW: Add files from filesystem folder to project group

USAGE: xcodeproj-cli add-folder [--project <project>] [--workspace <workspace>] [--verbose] [--dry-run] <folder-path> --group <group> --targets <targets> ... [--recursive] [--create-groups] [--no-create-groups]

ARGUMENTS:
  <folder-path>           Path to the folder containing files to add

OPTIONS:
  -p, --project <project> Path to .xcodeproj file (default: looks for
                          *.xcodeproj in current directory)
  -w, --workspace <workspace>
                          Path to .xcworkspace file
  -V, --verbose           Enable verbose output with performance metrics
  --dry-run               Preview changes without saving
  -g, --group <group>     Group to add the files to
  -t, --targets <targets> Target names to add files to
  -r, --recursive         Include files from subdirectories
  --create-groups         Create group hierarchy matching folder structure
                          (default behavior)
  --no-create-groups      Don't create group hierarchy
  --version               Show the version.
  -h, --help              Show help information.

